act.article:
2 
    Definitions.—In 
    these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,— 


a   ‘‘Act’’ means the Air (Prevention and 
    Control of Pollution) Act, 1981;


b   ‘‘Chairman’’ means the Chairman of the 
    Central Board;


c   ‘‘form’’ means a form set out in the 
    Schedules;


d   ‘‘meeting’’ means a meeting of the 
    Central Board or a meeting of Committee constituted by the Central Board;


e   ‘‘member-Secretary’’means the 
    member-Secretary of the Central Board;


f   ‘‘Schedule’’ means a schedule appended 
    to these rules;


g   ‘‘Section’’ means a section of the Act;


h   ‘‘Year’’ means the financial year 
    commencing on the Ist day of April;


i   words and expressions not defined in 
    these rules but defined in the Act shall have the meaning assigned to them 
    in the Act.
